issue.title: Local crashes upon terminating while downloading and restarting.
issue.body:
To reproduce:

1. Delete the local/software folder
1. Start remote
3. Start local
4. Terminate local (ctrl c) while software is downloading
5. restart local.

Here is the console printout of the error:
```
2017/05/29 11:19:58 Starting Local Server -> 127.0.0.1:8080
2017/05/29 11:19:58 Local IP: 192.168.1.34
2017/05/29 11:19:58 Hostname: soam-z87
panic: runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference
[signal SIGSEGV: segmentation violation code=0x1 addr=0x8 pc=0x67f279]

goroutine 1 [running]:
main.DownloadFromLocal(0xc4200fc540, 0xc42010c8c0, 0xc4201007b0, 0x10, 0x0, 0x0)
	/home/csinko/Projects/go/src/github.com/stohio/software-lab/local/main.go:320 +0x3b9
main.CheckOrDownload(0xc4200fa740, 0x2, 0x4, 0xc420108500)
	/home/csinko/Projects/go/src/github.com/stohio/software-lab/local/main.go:253 +0x46b
main.DownloadSoftware(0xc42012a000)
	/home/csinko/Projects/go/src/github.com/stohio/software-lab/local/main.go:228 +0x8e
main.main()
	/home/csinko/Projects/go/src/github.com/stohio/software-lab/local/main.go:123 +0x750
```

issue.title: [Feature Request] Requesting Software
issue.body:
Implement software requests. 

1. User tries to download software from our platform
2. Platform responds that the software does not exist
3. User requests the software to be installed (maybe give us a URL?) 
4. We download the software, register it to our platform
5. Now anyone can download the software at fast speeds
